data.name: cmbReshowDelay.ToolTip
data.value: The period, in milliseconds, that must transpire before subsequent tooltip windows appear as the mouse pointer moves from one tooltip region to another

data.name: cmbInitialDelay.ToolTip
data.value: The period of time, in milliseconds, that the mouse pointer must remain stationary within the tooltip region before the tooltip text is displayed

data.name: cmbAutoPopDelay.ToolTip
data.value: The period of time, in milliseconds, that the tooltip remains visible when the mouse pointer is stationary within the tooltip region

data.name: cmbAutomaticDelay.ToolTip
data.value: The amount of time in milliseconds that passes before the tooltip is displayed

data.name: rdbShowAlwaysFalse.ToolTip
data.value: Indicates whether the tooltip window is displayed even when its parent control is not active

data.name: rdbShowAlwaysTrue.ToolTip
data.value: Indicates whether the tooltip window is displayed even when its parent control is not active

data.name: rdbActivateFalse.ToolTip
data.value: Indicates whether the ToolTip control is currently active

data.name: rdbActivateTrue.ToolTip
data.value: Indicates whether the ToolTip control is currently active
